1
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:11,267
From now on,
I am here for you.

2
00:00:11,400 --> 00:00:14,400
I will no longer allow
you to carry everything alone.

3
00:00:14,533 --> 00:00:15,533
Finally, some good news!

4
00:00:15,667 --> 00:00:17,167
They said Jobert has woken up.

5
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:19,833
Thea is bad. I fell.

6
00:00:19,967 --> 00:00:21,533
She let go of me.

7
00:00:21,667 --> 00:00:23,367
My child, help me, please.

8
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:25,100
What kind of help do you need?

9
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:26,267
What did you do to my sibling?

10
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,300
Or are you going to kill
my sibling too?

11
00:00:28,433 --> 00:00:30,100
Mom, do not believe her.

12
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:32,967
- You have no shame!
- [CLAMORING]

13
00:01:16,833 --> 00:01:18,533
My child, forgive me.

14
00:01:22,167 --> 00:01:26,300
I was not here
when you needed me.

15
00:01:26,433 --> 00:01:28,300
I promised...

16
00:01:28,433 --> 00:01:30,567
I would not leave you,

17
00:01:30,700 --> 00:01:32,333
but I left you.

18
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,333
I left you and your sister.

19
00:01:37,467 --> 00:01:39,033
I left all of you...

20
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:45,367
and that was the most painful
thing I ever did.

21
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:46,767
But Jobert...

22
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:50,267
Mom is here now.

23
00:01:55,633 --> 00:01:56,933
I will not leave you again.

24
00:01:58,900 --> 00:02:00,867
I am here now, my child.

25
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,700
No matter what happens.

26
00:02:04,733 --> 00:02:07,367
[EVELYN SOBS]

27
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:09,767
My child, I am begging you.

28
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:14,933
My child!

29
00:02:16,067 --> 00:02:18,167
My child, please wake up!

30
00:02:22,433 --> 00:02:24,467
Mom loves you very much.

31
00:02:26,933 --> 00:02:34,200
Your sister and I
love you very much.

32
00:02:34,333 --> 00:02:36,567
My child,
please do not leave us!

33
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:46,667
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

34
00:02:54,267 --> 00:02:55,533
Why is it like this, Mom?

35
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:00,167
The trials keep coming
one after another.

36
00:03:03,567 --> 00:03:06,267
I do not know why
this is happening to me.

37
00:03:07,633 --> 00:03:08,900
I am not doing anything wrong,

38
00:03:09,033 --> 00:03:11,767
yet something bad
always happens.

39
00:03:16,567 --> 00:03:18,167
Sometimes, I feel like...

40
00:03:19,567 --> 00:03:21,233
I am absorbing everything.

41
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:24,467
I need to stay strong.

42
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:27,767
It is exhausting too.

43
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,600
My child...

44
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,967
I know you were...

45
00:03:40,100 --> 00:03:43,000
forced to be strong on your own.

46
00:03:48,867 --> 00:03:49,867
But...

47
00:03:52,367 --> 00:03:54,100
my child, I am here now.

48
00:03:58,967 --> 00:04:01,600
I should have done this
a long time ago.

49
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:07,800
My child...

50
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:12,000
from now on...

51
00:04:14,167 --> 00:04:15,167
I promise...

52
00:04:16,867 --> 00:04:20,667
I am here for you.

53
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,500
My child,

54
00:04:22,633 --> 00:04:26,100
I will no longer allow you
to carry everything alone.

55
00:04:28,267 --> 00:04:38,233
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

56
00:04:53,667 --> 00:05:03,633
[INTENSE MUSIC]

57
00:05:03,867 --> 00:05:08,300
[WHIMPERS]

58
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:10,800
- Jobert?
- [WHIMPERS]

59
00:05:10,933 --> 00:05:13,767
- Jobert!
- My God, thank you!

60
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:15,267
Doctor!

61
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:16,700
[SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

62
00:05:16,833 --> 00:05:19,600
Just a moment, Mom,
I will make a call.

63
00:05:19,733 --> 00:05:21,367
Doctor!

64
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:26,200
[SOBBING]
Jobert! My child.

65
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:27,500
Jobert!

66
00:05:27,633 --> 00:05:33,667
[SOBBING]
[INTENSE]

67
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,300
We are staying in the attic now?

68
00:05:37,067 --> 00:05:38,033
What?

69
00:05:38,167 --> 00:05:39,867
We are on the same level
as the house staff now?

70
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:42,933
We really cannot eat with them?

71
00:05:43,067 --> 00:05:44,167
So what?

72
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:45,600
You want to show yourself
to them

73
00:05:45,733 --> 00:05:47,667
after Mom called you out?

74
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,867
She told me earlier
when I arrived.

75
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,733
She said you fought
with Marj again.

76
00:05:51,867 --> 00:05:52,933
Wow!

77
00:05:53,067 --> 00:05:55,467
So, I am the villain again?

78
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,633
I am trying to make up
for it,

79
00:05:56,767 --> 00:05:58,800
but why am I still wrong?

80
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:02,300
Then get used to it.

81
00:06:02,433 --> 00:06:03,633
You are the one who insisted

82
00:06:03,767 --> 00:06:06,467
on forcing yourself
into this house, right?

83
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:09,933
You chose to stay here
even if it is difficult.

84
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:12,100
Because if you ask me...

85
00:06:12,233 --> 00:06:14,000
I would have left this place
long ago.

86
00:06:14,133 --> 00:06:15,733
This house...

87
00:06:15,867 --> 00:06:16,867
and you.

88
00:06:18,833 --> 00:06:21,100
You make it sound so easy
to say that to me.

89
00:06:22,933 --> 00:06:26,000
It is hard when you keep
making mistakes

90
00:06:26,133 --> 00:06:28,500
and Ashley and I take the fall
every time.

91
00:06:28,633 --> 00:06:30,900
[MELLOW MUSIC]

92
00:06:31,033 --> 00:06:32,133
[PHONE CHIMES]

93
00:06:32,267 --> 00:06:40,400
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

94
00:06:40,533 --> 00:06:41,633
Finally!

95
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:42,800
Some good news!

96
00:06:44,933 --> 00:06:46,233
They said Jobert has woken up.

97
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:48,633
Oh my God!

98
00:06:51,667 --> 00:06:53,233
Thank God!

99
00:06:53,367 --> 00:06:56,533
Dad, I will text Jasmine.
I will tell her the good news.

100
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:57,567
Go ahead, my child!

101
00:06:57,700 --> 00:06:59,067
All right.

102
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:09,033
[INTENSE MUSIC]

103
00:07:09,167 --> 00:07:10,367
What happened to you?

104
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:14,967
[INTENSE MUSIC]

105
00:07:15,133 --> 00:07:17,633
Nothing, I was just surprised.

106
00:07:18,867 --> 00:07:21,100
So Jobert is awake now.

107
00:07:21,233 --> 00:07:31,200
Good for them.

108
00:07:38,233 --> 00:07:39,967
Here, my child, the doctor
is just checking on him.

109
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:42,500
I will update you again later.

110
00:07:42,633 --> 00:07:45,600
There, say bye to Jobert now.

111
00:07:45,733 --> 00:07:55,700
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

112
00:07:56,333 --> 00:07:58,667
His vitals are stable.

113
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:02,867
But he is very sensitive to loud
sounds and sudden movements.

114
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,200
So...

115
00:08:04,333 --> 00:08:08,867
only gentle stimulation
and no sudden surprises.

116
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,300
We will be careful, Doctor.

117
00:08:10,433 --> 00:08:14,267
Okay, if he remembers fragments,
that is fine.

118
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,567
It is normal.

119
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:16,933
Do not push him...

120
00:08:17,067 --> 00:08:20,100
and let him speak
at his own pace.

121
00:08:20,233 --> 00:08:21,600
Thank you very much.

122
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,767
Oh!

123
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:34,533
[SCREAMING]

124
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:35,967
Do not let go!

125
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:38,767
- Do not let go!
- Jobert...

126
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:40,200
- Do not let go!
- Stay calm.

127
00:08:40,333 --> 00:08:42,433
We are here. Mom is here.

128
00:08:42,567 --> 00:08:46,867
[WHIMPERING]
Do not...

129
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:50,300
Let go?

130
00:08:50,433 --> 00:08:51,367
What? Who let go?

131
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,467
Who? What let go?

132
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:58,167
I told Sister,
so she let go of me!

133
00:08:58,333 --> 00:08:59,233
I fell.

134
00:08:59,367 --> 00:09:01,700
Bad...

135
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:03,033
What?

136
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:04,300
Who? What let go?

137
00:09:04,433 --> 00:09:06,000
Who let go, Jobert?

138
00:09:08,467 --> 00:09:09,367
<i> Let go.</i>

139
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:13,967
<i>Sister let go of me, so I fell.</i>

140
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:16,167
Which sister? Me, Marj?

141
00:09:16,300 --> 00:09:18,300
I, let go?

142
00:09:18,433 --> 00:09:20,933
Sister let go of me.

143
00:09:21,067 --> 00:09:22,967
Thea is bad.

144
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,300
<i> Jobert!</i>

145
00:09:29,433 --> 00:09:30,767
I fell.

146
00:09:30,900 --> 00:09:33,100
She let go of me.

147
00:09:33,233 --> 00:09:34,500
My God.

148
00:09:36,533 --> 00:09:42,233
[INTENSE MUSIC]

149
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:46,333
Wait a moment, Jobert, okay? Let
us take this one step at a time.

150
00:09:46,467 --> 00:09:49,133
What were you doing
before you fell?

151
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:58,133
Pong and I were making a video
with Ashley.

152
00:09:58,267 --> 00:10:02,933
<i>Then you just click this here
to start recording.</i>

153
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:04,233
Then...

154
00:10:04,367 --> 00:10:05,767
Ashley left.

155
00:10:05,900 --> 00:10:08,267
She said she would be back.
It would be quick.

156
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:11,267
Pong and I were left alone.

157
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:13,700
Then we walked around.

158
00:10:13,833 --> 00:10:16,000
Pong and I
were recording videos.

159
00:10:16,133 --> 00:10:17,967
Then...

160
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:20,167
Then what happened, my child?

161
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:21,700
Then...

162
00:10:26,900 --> 00:10:33,000
I saw kind brother and Thea.

163
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:34,467
[THEA MOANING IN DISTANCE]

164
00:10:34,633 --> 00:10:36,500
<i> Kind Brother...</i>

165
00:10:41,967 --> 00:10:43,600
What?

166
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:45,567
I was surprised.

167
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:50,800
- I got scared, so I ran.
<i> - Jobert!</i>

168
00:10:50,933 --> 00:10:52,367
That is why you ran?

169
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:53,400
Yes.

170
00:10:54,967 --> 00:10:56,400
Then...

171
00:10:56,533 --> 00:10:58,300
I fell.

172
00:10:58,433 --> 00:10:59,967
No one picked me up.

173
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:03,100
Then I saw sister Thea.

174
00:11:03,233 --> 00:11:04,600
[INTENSE]

175
00:11:04,733 --> 00:11:07,200
<i>Do not wait for me
to get angry at you!</i>

176
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,767
<i> Give me your cellphone!</i>

177
00:11:08,933 --> 00:11:13,233
<i> - Where is it?
-</i> [CLAMORING]

178
00:11:13,367 --> 00:11:14,500
What did she do?

179
00:11:16,667 --> 00:11:19,000
She wanted to take
Jobert's phone.

180
00:11:19,133 --> 00:11:20,833
I did not want to.

181
00:11:20,967 --> 00:11:23,300
She is bad. Bad!

182
00:11:23,433 --> 00:11:24,933
Jobert, where were you then?

183
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,900
On the...

184
00:11:29,033 --> 00:11:32,367
stairs.
I was about to fall.

185
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:33,700
I fell.

186
00:11:33,833 --> 00:11:37,867
But Thea picked me up.

187
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,767
She picked me up.

188
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:44,667
She held my shirt here,
then nothing...

189
00:11:44,833 --> 00:11:47,867
I thought she would help me.

190
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:52,333
But she did not,
because I shouted and said...

191
00:11:52,467 --> 00:11:55,033
<i> I will tell this to my sister.</i>

192
00:11:55,167 --> 00:11:57,100
Then she really let go.

193
00:11:57,233 --> 00:12:00,433
[INTENSE MUSIC]

194
00:12:00,567 --> 00:12:01,867
<i> Jobert!</i>

195
00:12:03,067 --> 00:12:13,033
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

196
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:15,500
That is why I fell.

197
00:12:15,667 --> 00:12:17,200
She really let go of you?

198
00:12:17,333 --> 00:12:18,933
Yes.

199
00:12:19,067 --> 00:12:20,267
I fell.

200
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,333
Mom, did you hear that?

201
00:12:21,467 --> 00:12:23,700
Yes, I heard that, Marj.

202
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:26,400
If she can do this
to my sibling,

203
00:12:26,533 --> 00:12:29,500
what else can she do
to save herself?

204
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:35,833
She is bad, Sis.

205
00:12:35,967 --> 00:12:45,933
[INTENSE MUSIC]

206
00:12:49,900 --> 00:12:51,467
Mom.

207
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:54,967
Is it okay
if I go with Dad later?

208
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:56,233
Where are you going?

209
00:12:56,367 --> 00:12:58,667
We are just visiting
Uncle Jobert.

210
00:13:06,767 --> 00:13:09,567
You are really kind, you know?

211
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:13,933
Even with everything happening,
you still think about them.

212
00:13:15,033 --> 00:13:17,567
Mom, seriously?

213
00:13:21,533 --> 00:13:24,467
Do you want this family
to fall apart?

214
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:27,033
Is it not already broken?

215
00:13:27,167 --> 00:13:29,900
But do you want it
to break even more?

216
00:13:30,033 --> 00:13:31,800
Of course not, Mom!

217
00:13:31,933 --> 00:13:35,133
But why are you asking me
these questions?

218
00:13:36,233 --> 00:13:37,433
[SIGHS]

219
00:13:40,333 --> 00:13:43,567
I do not want this family
to fall apart.

220
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:46,233
You are all I have left.

221
00:13:46,367 --> 00:13:49,800
You are my family.

222
00:13:49,933 --> 00:13:52,267
Mom, why do you sound so scared?

223
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:54,100
Why? Is there a problem?

224
00:13:54,233 --> 00:13:55,567
Is there another problem?

225
00:13:58,933 --> 00:14:02,000
Yes.

226
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:05,533
My child, help me, please.

227
00:14:05,667 --> 00:14:06,833
What?

228
00:14:06,967 --> 00:14:08,567
I need your help.

229
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:14,033
Mom, how?

230
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:16,767
What help do you need?

231
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:24,400
Marj!

232
00:14:24,533 --> 00:14:26,133
Marj!
[SPEAKS IN VISAYAN LANGUAGE]

233
00:14:26,267 --> 00:14:27,467
I will confront Thea, Mom.

234
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:30,233
If I have to push her down
the stairs myself, I will do it.

235
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:32,800
Marj!
[SPEAKS IN VISAYAN LANGUAGE]

236
00:14:32,933 --> 00:14:34,900
This cannot be like this.

237
00:14:35,033 --> 00:14:36,900
We have no evidence.

238
00:14:37,033 --> 00:14:39,767
All we have is Jobert's story.

239
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:43,233
Mom, my sibling is not lying.
I know him.

240
00:14:43,367 --> 00:14:46,167
I am not saying he is lying.

241
00:14:46,300 --> 00:14:48,000
But what are you going to do?

242
00:14:48,133 --> 00:14:50,000
What if you confront her
right now?

243
00:14:50,133 --> 00:14:51,200
What?
[SPEAKS IN VISAYAN LANGUAGE]

244
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:52,500
Will you fight her?

245
00:14:52,633 --> 00:14:54,700
Do you think she will confess?

246
00:14:54,833 --> 00:14:57,567
I know why they did this
to Jobert.

247
00:14:57,700 --> 00:15:00,167
They want to silence my sibling.

248
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:04,867
Mom, Jobert saw what they did.

249
00:15:05,033 --> 00:15:09,800
I cannot stay here knowing
someone did this to my sibling.

250
00:15:13,433 --> 00:15:15,267
All right, Marj.

251
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:18,133
Marj, be careful.

252
00:15:18,267 --> 00:15:20,600
[SPEAKS IN VISAYAN LANGUAGE]

253
00:15:20,733 --> 00:15:21,800
Go on, Marj.

254
00:15:21,933 --> 00:15:31,900
[INTENSE MUSIC]

255
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:52,767
Mom, I made your favorite
jasmine tea.

256
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:58,533
I do not need
your peace offering.

257
00:15:58,667 --> 00:16:00,933
And please do not call me Mom.

258
00:16:01,067 --> 00:16:04,533
Because Paolo and Edward
are my only children.

259
00:16:04,667 --> 00:16:07,700
I do not remember
delivering a homewrecker

260
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:10,767
in the VIP ward
of St. Bernadette Hospital.

261
00:16:14,733 --> 00:16:17,533
Mom, I am truly sorry.

262
00:16:17,667 --> 00:16:22,233
I know that whatever I say,
it is too late.

263
00:16:22,367 --> 00:16:25,333
If I could take everything back,
I would.

264
00:16:27,233 --> 00:16:29,767
- What did you do to my sibling?
- What?

265
00:16:29,900 --> 00:16:32,367
Can you undo what you did
to Jobert?

266
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:33,600
What?

267
00:16:33,733 --> 00:16:34,967
What are you talking about,
Marj?

268
00:16:35,100 --> 00:16:36,467
Do you have demon blood?

269
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:39,567
Why do you enjoy doing evil?

270
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:42,467
You were not satisfied
with stealing my spouse,

271
00:16:42,633 --> 00:16:44,667
now you want
to kill my sibling too?

272
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:47,167
What the hell are you
talking about, Marj?

273
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:49,600
Marj, I do not know
what you are talking about!

274
00:16:49,733 --> 00:16:51,233
Mom, do not believe her.

275
00:16:51,367 --> 00:16:52,500
She has gone crazy.

276
00:16:52,633 --> 00:16:54,200
What? You are still denying it?

277
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:56,300
Jobert himself told me.

278
00:16:56,433 --> 00:16:59,100
You let him fall down
the stairs.

279
00:16:59,233 --> 00:17:00,933
You have no shame!

280
00:17:01,067 --> 00:17:03,733
[CLAMORING]
You animal!

281
00:17:03,867 --> 00:17:06,667
You animal!
[CLAMORING]

282
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:07,833
Ma'am Marj!

283
00:17:07,967 --> 00:17:10,333
Ma'am Marj, please calm down!

284
00:17:10,467 --> 00:17:12,967
Let them be!

285
00:17:13,100 --> 00:17:14,933
[CLAMORING]
You demon!

286
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:20,500
[INTENSE MUSIC]

287
00:17:21,167 --> 00:17:22,167
I did nothing wrong!

288
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:24,033
Marj! Marj! Thea!

289
00:17:24,167 --> 00:17:26,633
Stop it! Stop! Stop!

290
00:17:26,767 --> 00:17:28,400
Stop it!

291
00:17:28,533 --> 00:17:29,367
- Enough!
- You have no shame!

292
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:31,533
I will charge you
with attempted murder!

293
00:17:31,667 --> 00:17:32,833
What? Murder?

294
00:17:32,967 --> 00:17:35,333
Do you know what she did
to my sibling?

295
00:17:35,467 --> 00:17:37,333
Jobert already told me
everything!

296
00:17:37,467 --> 00:17:39,133
Especially what you did to him!

297
00:17:39,267 --> 00:17:40,800
Marj!

298
00:17:40,933 --> 00:17:42,900
Stop blaming me, Marj!

299
00:17:43,033 --> 00:17:44,600
I am innocent!

300
00:17:44,733 --> 00:17:46,167
And how could I let go

301
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:47,000
when I was not even there

302
00:17:47,133 --> 00:17:49,067
- where he fell?
- You are lying!

303
00:17:49,233 --> 00:17:51,133
- Enough!
- I'm innocent.

304
00:17:51,267 --> 00:17:52,700
- Enough, please!
- Enough!

305
00:17:52,833 --> 00:17:53,867
Enough!

306
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:55,567
[EERIE MUSIC]

307
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:57,100
I was there!

308
00:17:57,233 --> 00:18:02,267
[INTENSE MUSIC]

309
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:04,400
I saw Uncle Jobert.

310
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,867
I left him
just to get something.

311
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:09,367
Then he suddenly disappeared,

312
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:13,067
but I looked for him and found
him at the bottom of the stairs.

313
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,400
[INTENSE MUSIC]

314
00:18:14,533 --> 00:18:16,367
- What?
- Jobert slipped,

315
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:18,967
that is why he fell, Aunt Marj.

316
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:21,800
What? I did not see anyone else
pass by there.

317
00:18:21,967 --> 00:18:23,733
- No.
- When I went to Uncle Jobert,

318
00:18:23,867 --> 00:18:25,333
- that was when Mom arrived.
- No.

319
00:18:25,467 --> 00:18:26,700
You are not telling the truth!

320
00:18:26,833 --> 00:18:28,700
My sibling is not a liar!

321
00:18:28,833 --> 00:18:29,833
- Marj.
- And what?

322
00:18:29,967 --> 00:18:31,667
My daughter is lying?

323
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:34,933
Marj, enough!
You do not have any evidence!

324
00:18:35,067 --> 00:18:37,333
Then I will find some!

325
00:18:37,467 --> 00:18:39,033
I will find it!

326
00:18:39,167 --> 00:18:42,067
You think this is over
because the child lied for you?

327
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:44,167
We are not done, Thea!

328
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:46,133
You will pay for this,
I am telling you!

329
00:18:46,267 --> 00:18:56,233
[INTENSE MUSIC]

330
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:05,533
It is a good thing

331
00:19:05,667 --> 00:19:08,933
I assigned the Menagerie Project
to Mr. Castello.

332
00:19:10,267 --> 00:19:12,367
With your recent scandal,

333
00:19:13,667 --> 00:19:16,300
it would likely be harder
to sell

334
00:19:16,433 --> 00:19:18,767
if you were still handling it.

335
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:22,033
Dad, can we just go home
in peace?

336
00:19:22,167 --> 00:19:23,500
I had a long day.

337
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:26,100
Please, do not lecture me
anymore.

338
00:19:27,233 --> 00:19:28,433
Can you blame me?

339
00:19:30,167 --> 00:19:31,367
Even if we avoid the press,

340
00:19:33,167 --> 00:19:35,300
our name is still circulating.

341
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,000
Your name.

342
00:19:38,133 --> 00:19:40,367
You told me yourself.

343
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:43,567
No comment at all costs.

344
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:46,233
How am I supposed to clear
my name?

345
00:19:46,367 --> 00:19:47,800
[HUFFS]

346
00:19:47,933 --> 00:19:51,300
And how would you do that
if you are actually guilty?

347
00:19:53,467 --> 00:19:55,967
This company is my legacy,
Paolo.

348
00:19:57,600 --> 00:19:58,967
And now...

349
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:04,200
everything could disappear

350
00:20:04,333 --> 00:20:06,767
because of your
and Thea's recklessness.

351
00:20:06,900 --> 00:20:08,567
You do not know
how to be careful.

352
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:12,267
After I fixed it before,

353
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:14,067
you still did not learn.

354
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:16,767
Dad...

355
00:20:16,900 --> 00:20:18,800
I did not mean
for the video to happen.

356
00:20:20,267 --> 00:20:22,867
This is no longer just about...

357
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:26,233
your affair with Thea.

358
00:20:26,367 --> 00:20:28,267
Paolo...

359
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:30,233
I am afraid...

360
00:20:30,367 --> 00:20:33,267
Marj has opened a Pandora's box.

361
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:36,700
And you know what that means.

362
00:20:38,433 --> 00:20:42,600
The things we hid before
will come out.

363
00:20:44,067 --> 00:20:45,467
Just get to the point, Dad.

364
00:20:49,233 --> 00:20:51,167
Oscar...

365
00:20:51,300 --> 00:20:53,000
step aside.

366
00:20:53,133 --> 00:20:54,900
Step outside for now.

367
00:20:55,033 --> 00:20:56,233
All right, Sir.

368
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:15,033
What do you think will happen

369
00:21:15,167 --> 00:21:17,333
when Marj finds out you have
been lying for a long time

370
00:21:17,467 --> 00:21:18,967
about Ashley,

371
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:20,333
your child?

372
00:21:21,300 --> 00:21:23,233
That would be a bigger scandal.

373
00:21:24,333 --> 00:21:26,000
It will not just affect
the family.

374
00:21:27,433 --> 00:21:28,733
The company.

375
00:21:30,033 --> 00:21:31,800
My legacy, Paolo.

376
00:21:35,467 --> 00:21:37,600
So, make sure...

377
00:21:37,733 --> 00:21:40,400
Marj never finds out,
or else ...

378
00:21:41,433 --> 00:21:44,867
everything I worked for
will go to charity.

379
00:21:46,133 --> 00:21:48,267
Because I will no
longer have an heir.

380
00:21:49,767 --> 00:21:51,467
And Ashley?

381
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:53,267
She is protected...

382
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,700
as long as you stay silent.

383
00:21:58,200 --> 00:22:00,767
While her true identity
remains a secret.

384
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:10,100
[INTENSE MUSIC]

385
00:22:19,367 --> 00:22:20,533
Love.

386
00:22:20,667 --> 00:22:25,467
[PENSIVE MUSIC]

387
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:26,833
Hi, love.

388
00:22:27,967 --> 00:22:29,600
Do you know something?

389
00:22:32,033 --> 00:22:33,667
Know something?

390
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:34,967
What are you talking about?

391
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:41,000
Did you and Thea plan it?

392
00:22:41,133 --> 00:22:43,967
Did you agree with her
to make my sibling fall?

393
00:22:44,100 --> 00:22:45,667
Or was it done in the heat
of the moment

394
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:47,433
because you had no choice

395
00:22:47,567 --> 00:22:50,433
but to silence my sibling
after seeing you?

396
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:51,900
Wait. Wait, Marj.

397
00:22:52,933 --> 00:22:56,933
Marj, Jobert's fall
was an accident.

398
00:22:57,067 --> 00:22:58,467
I did not have anything to do
with it.

399
00:22:58,600 --> 00:23:01,433
And as far as I know,
Thea was not there either.

400
00:23:01,567 --> 00:23:04,967
Jobert said Thea
was the reason he got hurt.

401
00:23:05,100 --> 00:23:07,200
Your shameless mistress
did it on purpose.

402
00:23:08,967 --> 00:23:11,533
Marj, believe me.
I know nothing about that.

403
00:23:11,667 --> 00:23:13,767
I am telling you the truth.

404
00:23:13,900 --> 00:23:15,933
How can I trust you?

405
00:23:16,067 --> 00:23:18,033
You have lied to me
so many times.

406
00:23:18,167 --> 00:23:20,000
Are you still
hiding something?

407
00:23:20,133 --> 00:23:22,567
Do you still have secrets
I do not know about?

408
00:23:26,233 --> 00:23:27,933
None.

409
00:23:28,067 --> 00:23:30,533
I am not hiding anything
from you anymore.

410
00:23:30,667 --> 00:23:32,400
Just make sure of that.

411
00:23:32,533 --> 00:23:35,833
Because the moment I find
out you are still lying,

412
00:23:35,967 --> 00:23:37,467
we are done, Paolo.

413
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:41,333
And you are done
as a father too.

414
00:23:41,467 --> 00:23:51,433
[INTENSE MUSIC]

415
00:24:00,467 --> 00:24:10,433
[UNSETTLING MUSIC]

416
00:24:14,033 --> 00:24:15,133
My child.

417
00:24:16,433 --> 00:24:18,100
I know what you
did was difficult.

418
00:24:19,667 --> 00:24:22,233
But thank you
for helping me.

419
00:24:26,867 --> 00:24:28,867
[SIGHS]

420
00:24:29,033 --> 00:24:31,800
I feel guilty
about what I did, Mom.

421
00:24:33,967 --> 00:24:35,533
[SIGHS]

422
00:24:35,667 --> 00:24:38,700
My child, you only did
what needed to be done.

423
00:24:38,833 --> 00:24:40,533
For our family.

424
00:24:41,900 --> 00:24:44,433
And thank you for protecting me.

425
00:24:49,167 --> 00:24:51,000
[SIGHS]

426
00:24:55,233 --> 00:24:59,233
Do you really have no fault
at all, Mom?

427
00:24:59,367 --> 00:25:06,033
[INTENSE MUSIC]
